OL,3,C'We're devastated': Minibus stolen
OL,4,Cfrom autism charity
OL,6,F"And it's not just us ` other NEAS
OL,7,Fservices use the van too. Nearby
OL,8,Fchildren's homes use it in emergencies
OL,9,Fwhen a child is poorly in school, and
OL,10,Fthere's a young man in supported
OL,11,Fliving nearby who regularly uses it.
OL,13,F"All that has been taken away from us."
OL,15,FPeter Mountain, operations manager for
OL,16,FNEAS residential homes, said the
OL,17,Fminibuses were vital for the children,
OL,18,Fyoung people and adults the charity
OL,19,Fsupports.
